But now for some short and fast comments on Saxonia from my side...

The panels are great for A500 times, although they are outdated these days and could cause bad words by younger people. I like them! Though I recommend to find another artist or ask µC5MalsmisµC4 for something fresher (he can be do very high quality stuff) for the next issue as I seem to be the only one who likes them! :-(

The code is stable and that it runs even on A500 makes it something special. Keep up the spirit! :-) (The only thing that should change is the text routine! Displaying empty screens when no article is available does not look good.)

Articles are mixed. Some are really interesting, others are simply fillers, a genre that is sadly needed these days with so low support! The coding articles might be great (and something new these days) but can not be judged by me as I am no coder! Thumbs up for the huge work µC5RumrunnerµC4 did! But the articles should be at least justified and topaz-font is not what I call good design.

